---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
	title="review skill"
	description="The review skill checks CSS against Tideway's tokens, semantic roles, and BEM conventions, reporting where it drifts."
	active="review"
>
	<article class="doc">
		<p class="doc__eyebrow">Skill</p>
		<h1 class="doc__title">review</h1>
		<p class="doc__lead">
			Checks CSS against the Tideway conventions and reports where it drifts — off-scale values,
			inlined tokens, direct palette use, and BEM or selector violations. It reads and reports;
			fixes happen only on your go-ahead.
		</p>

		<section class="doc__section">
			<h2 class="doc__section-title">What it checks</h2>
			<div class="doc__list">
				<p class="doc__item">
					<strong>Off-scale values</strong> — a color, spacing, size, radius, or shadow that isn't one
					of the <a class="doc__link" href="/docs/colors">token scales</a>.
				</p>
				<p class="doc__item">
					<strong>Inlined token values</strong> — a raw value that equals a token
					(<code class="doc__code">padding: 1rem</code>) instead of
					<code class="doc__code">var(--space-4)</code>.
				</p>
				<p class="doc__item">
					<strong>Direct palette use</strong> — a component reading a
					<code class="doc__code">--color-*</code> primitive for color instead of a
					<a class="doc__link" href="/docs/theming">semantic role</a>.
				</p>
				<p class="doc__item">
					<strong>BEM &amp; selector violations</strong> — names that aren't
					<code class="doc__code">block__element--modifier</code>, nested elements, multiple classes
					per selector, IDs, descendant combinators, or <code class="doc__code">!important</code>.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="doc__section">
			<h2 class="doc__section-title">Scope</h2>
			<div class="doc__list">
				<p class="doc__item">
					By default it reviews <strong>only what changed</strong> — the staged and unstaged edits
					(<code class="doc__code">git diff HEAD</code>), not the whole codebase.
				</p>
				<p class="doc__item">
					It widens to a full audit only when you ask, or when there are no pending changes — and in
					that case it asks first, since a whole-codebase review is a larger task.
				</p>
				<p class="doc__item">
					Findings are grouped by file and rule, with the fix named. Nothing is rewritten until you say
					so.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>
	</article>
</DocsLayout>
